WARRI – Hon. Monday Onovughakpor Edesiri, the Organising Secretary of ‘Campaign Flow’, a political pressure group in Delta State, has enjoined members of the group to be good ambassadors and be prepared towards the 2023 general elections. Edirisi, a PDP stalwart, gave the advice on Thursday when he inaugurated the Isoko South chapter at Olomoro, in Isoko South local government area of the state. Describing the inauguration as the dawn of a new era, Edesiri reminded the members to disregard money politics, insisting that the rightful person that would also be as great as Governor Ifeanyi Okowa should be voted for as the incoming governor. “What we are doing today is for the progress and prosperity of the state. However, I plead with you to be hard working so that the PDP will continue to rule the state in every election,” he added. Earlier, the group’s coordinator of the grup in the locality Hon. Whisky Ewubareh, commended Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and the Campaign Flow Director-General, Engr. (Dr.) Bemigho Ofoeyeno, for their hard work and commitment towards the development of the state. “In the history of the creation of Delta State, Isoko South Local Government Area, has never lost out in any election, and I assure you all that not in my time of leadership will the area lose any election, in regards to the fact that I have painstakingly drawn my executives and coordinators across the local government area to ensure that the results are accomplished stressed the coordinator,” he stressed.